00:10:12.712 --> 00:10:14.480 align:middle line:84%
in a sense you're
saving yourself,

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:17.116 align:middle line:84%
you're saving your own
reality on some level.

00:10:17.116 --> 00:10:18.484 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: Well, the
Greek mythologist,

00:10:18.484 --> 00:10:21.120 align:middle line:84%
Joseph Campbell said "The only
way you can explain why one

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:24.557 align:middle line:84%
person will be crazy enough to
do something like Autrey did is

00:10:24.557 --> 00:10:27.527 align:middle line:84%
that if those two
minds were so fused

00:10:27.527 --> 00:10:30.363 align:middle line:84%
that you became essentially
the same person as you say--

00:10:30.363 --> 00:10:31.464 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:10:31.464 --> 00:10:32.732 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: -- so that,
at the decisive moment,

00:10:32.732 --> 00:10:35.468 align:middle line:84%
the rescuer is not
rescuing someone else.

00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:38.271 align:middle line:84%
He's actually rescuing
himself so closely

00:10:38.271 --> 00:10:41.307 align:middle line:84%
and so tightly have their
consciousness come together."

00:10:41.307 --> 00:10:42.508 align:middle line:90%
I think that's spot on.

00:10:42.508 --> 00:10:45.244 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And it had to
have been something having

00:10:45.244 --> 00:10:46.679 align:middle line:90%
to do with compassion?

00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:47.714 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Yes.

00:10:47.714 --> 00:10:49.716 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: That is
a universal solvent.

00:10:49.716 --> 00:10:51.084 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Yes, it is.

00:10:51.084 --> 00:10:55.455 align:middle line:84%
And I think that one reason
people have a really tough time,

00:10:55.455 --> 00:10:58.891 align:middle line:84%
wondering why people behave
like that is because it goes

00:10:58.891 --> 00:11:00.626 align:middle line:90%
against modern biology.

00:11:00.626 --> 00:11:03.096 align:middle line:84%
People aren't supposed to
put their life in danger

00:11:03.096 --> 00:11:05.865 align:middle line:84%
for somebody they don't have
anything in common with.

00:11:05.865 --> 00:11:06.999 align:middle line:90%
We're supposed--

00:11:06.999 --> 00:11:09.001 align:middle line:84%
so the biologists tell
us to conserve our genes

00:11:09.001 --> 00:11:12.605 align:middle line:84%
so we can stay alive and
propagate and convey our genes

00:11:12.605 --> 00:11:15.108 align:middle line:90%
down through other's generation.

00:11:15.108 --> 00:11:16.576 align:middle line:90%
So, this doesn't use that, no.

00:11:16.576 --> 00:11:19.412 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: I think one person
in particular, Richard Dawkins.

00:11:19.412 --> 00:11:21.481 align:middle line:90%
you know, the selfish gene.

00:11:21.481 --> 00:11:22.682 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Right.

00:11:22.682 --> 00:11:24.283 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: That's not
turning out to have legs.

00:11:24.283 --> 00:11:25.485 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: No.

00:11:25.485 --> 00:11:27.153 align:middle line:84%
And as a matter of fact,
he's taken a lot of heat,

00:11:27.153 --> 00:11:29.922 align:middle line:84%
deservedly so because
it's just doesn't account

00:11:29.922 --> 00:11:31.524 align:middle line:90%
for human experiences.

00:11:31.524 --> 00:11:34.127 align:middle line:90%
In the book I talked about--

00:11:34.127 --> 00:11:38.931 align:middle line:84%
an oppositional book to Dawkins'
the self-- selfish gene.

00:11:38.931 --> 00:11:42.335 align:middle line:84%
The name of this book
is the "Selfless Gene."

00:11:42.335 --> 00:11:45.004 align:middle line:84%
And so we really do need
to expand what we know

00:11:45.004 --> 00:11:48.808 align:middle line:84%
about human behavior because
Dawkins was willfully inadequate

00:11:48.808 --> 00:11:52.278 align:middle line:84%
in his assessment of who we
are and what we're capable of.

00:11:52.278 --> 00:11:53.379 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Absolutely.

00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:54.313 align:middle line:84%
Now, let's talk about
your own experience

00:11:54.313 --> 00:11:56.616 align:middle line:90%
within that in Vietnam.

00:11:56.616 --> 00:11:58.451 align:middle line:90%
You were platoon surgeon.

00:11:58.451 --> 00:12:01.187 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: Well, I was battalion
surgeon way up behind--

00:12:01.187 --> 00:12:04.223 align:middle line:84%
beyond anything as
fancy as a MASH unit.

00:12:04.223 --> 00:12:07.326 align:middle line:84%
One day a helicopter crashed
about a couple hundred yards

00:12:07.326 --> 00:12:11.998 align:middle line:84%
from my aid station and I ran to
the side, the thing was a mess.

00:12:11.998 --> 00:12:14.767 align:middle line:84%
It was turned upside down,
the pilot was trapped.

00:12:14.767 --> 00:12:17.904 align:middle line:84%
And without thinking, I
entered this helicopter

00:12:17.904 --> 00:12:21.574 align:middle line:84%
with the ruptured fuel
tanks, draining fuel,

00:12:21.574 --> 00:12:24.477 align:middle line:84%
and it was expected that it
will explode at any moment

00:12:24.477 --> 00:12:28.915 align:middle line:84%
and cut the pilot loose from
the seat belts and got him

00:12:28.915 --> 00:12:32.285 align:middle line:84%
out with the help of
the medic of mine.

00:12:32.285 --> 00:12:35.655 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't understand
later why I behave that way

00:12:35.655 --> 00:12:39.458 align:middle line:84%
because I'd made solemn vows
before I went to Vietnam

00:12:39.458 --> 00:12:44.197 align:middle line:84%
that I would never do anything
risky like that out of deference

00:12:44.197 --> 00:12:46.833 align:middle line:84%
to my family and the
people who cared for me

00:12:46.833 --> 00:12:50.203 align:middle line:84%
but when the situations
like that would crop up,

00:12:50.203 --> 00:12:53.906 align:middle line:84%
they were just action and
behavior and no thinking.

00:12:53.906 --> 00:12:56.676 align:middle line:90%
And it was automatic and I was--

00:12:56.676 --> 00:12:58.644 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: You were
cognizant of the danger.

00:12:58.644 --> 00:13:00.980 align:middle line:84%
You knew that it could
explode on some level.

00:13:00.980 --> 00:13:01.814 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Yeah.

00:13:01.814 --> 00:13:02.615 align:middle line:90%
It was hard not to be aware of.

00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:03.883 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah sure.

00:13:03.883 --> 00:13:05.251 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: There
were lot of soldiers

00:13:05.251 --> 00:13:08.421 align:middle line:84%
who were ringing this thing
and it kept out of the danger

00:13:08.421 --> 00:13:11.691 align:middle line:84%
with the expectation that, you
know, they could be blown up.

00:13:11.691 --> 00:13:13.726 align:middle line:84%
And I remember to this
day when I rotated back

00:13:13.726 --> 00:13:14.994 align:middle line:90%
to the United States

00:13:14.994 --> 00:13:18.331 align:middle line:84%
of encountering Joseph
Campbell's description of how

00:13:18.331 --> 00:13:21.667 align:middle line:84%
at those decisive moments when
one person rescues another

00:13:21.667 --> 00:13:25.805 align:middle line:84%
as we have mentioned,
the consciousness fuses,

00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:27.707 align:middle line:90%
so that there is not thought.

00:13:27.707 --> 00:13:31.777 align:middle line:84%
There is no careful
weighing of circumstances.

00:13:31.777 --> 00:13:33.212 align:middle line:90%
There's only action.

00:13:33.212 --> 00:13:34.747 align:middle line:84%
And I knew in an
heartbeat, Regina that,

00:13:34.747 --> 00:13:37.483 align:middle line:84%
that was the explanation
for my crazy behavior,

00:13:37.483 --> 00:13:39.151 align:middle line:90%
and I still believe that

00:13:39.151 --> 00:13:43.289 align:middle line:84%
and I think that's the best most
rational explanation we have

00:13:43.289 --> 00:13:45.358 align:middle line:90%
about heroic act to that sort.

00:13:45.358 --> 00:13:47.493 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Is that one of the
things that motivated you to go

00:13:47.493 --> 00:13:52.164 align:middle line:84%
down this path of understanding
deeper this interconnectedness

00:13:52.164 --> 00:13:52.932 align:middle line:90%
of mind?

00:13:52.932 --> 00:13:54.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Oh absolutely.

00:13:54.200 --> 00:13:55.334 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: A pivotal-- I
assumed it was a pivotal event

00:13:55.334 --> 00:13:55.968 align:middle line:90%
in your life.

00:13:55.968 --> 00:13:57.203 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: It was.

00:13:57.203 --> 00:13:58.004 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And you must
have witnessed it thousands

00:13:58.004 --> 00:13:59.305 align:middle line:90%
of times out there.

00:13:59.305 --> 00:14:01.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: Quite a number of
times as a matter of fact.

00:14:01.240 --> 00:14:03.910 align:middle line:84%
But there was another event
that I should put on the table.

00:14:03.910 --> 00:14:06.212 align:middle line:84%
I've known about this
connectedness thing ever

00:14:06.212 --> 00:14:10.416 align:middle line:84%
since I was old enough to know
that I am an identical twin.

00:14:10.416 --> 00:14:13.986 align:middle line:84%
And my brother and I have
had this sort of thing all

00:14:13.986 --> 00:14:17.189 align:middle line:84%
of their life, we just
call it twin stuff.

00:14:17.189 --> 00:14:21.327 align:middle line:84%
It's the distant appreciation
of someone else's thoughts

00:14:21.327 --> 00:14:25.798 align:middle line:84%
and emotion and sometimes
sharing even physical symptoms.

00:14:25.798 --> 00:14:29.135 align:middle line:84%
When you don't know that
your identical twin is having

00:14:29.135 --> 00:14:30.236 align:middle line:90%
something like that.

00:14:30.236 --> 00:14:31.504 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:14:31.504 --> 00:14:34.573 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: These are jaw
dropping experiences, really.

00:14:34.573 --> 00:14:36.642 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: I have a big chunk
in this interview to talk

00:14:36.642 --> 00:14:39.145 align:middle line:84%
about you two and there's
even more to that story

00:14:39.145 --> 00:14:41.013 align:middle line:90%
and some other people as well.

00:14:41.013 --> 00:14:44.050 align:middle line:84%
But something has caught my mind
here, within this, before we get

00:14:44.050 --> 00:14:47.887 align:middle line:84%
into the twin phenomena and
I love the animal phenomena.

00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:49.188 align:middle line:90%
The animal kingdom is so pure--

00:14:49.188 --> 00:14:49.889 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: So do I.

00:14:49.889 --> 00:14:50.957 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: -- that way.

00:14:50.957 --> 00:14:52.358 align:middle line:84%
We are going to some
videos on that too.

00:14:52.358 --> 00:14:55.628 align:middle line:84%
But one thing that striking
me is when you're talking

00:14:55.628 --> 00:14:59.398 align:middle line:84%
about this, no thinking,
this fusion of mind

00:14:59.398 --> 00:15:03.736 align:middle line:84%
in these heroic events,
I'm looking in my mind

00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:08.641 align:middle line:84%
at the converse effect which
I interviewed a woman named

00:15:08.641 --> 00:15:10.876 align:middle line:90%
Elena Tonetti-Vladimirova.

00:15:10.876 --> 00:15:14.847 align:middle line:90%
She had become the protege of--

00:15:14.847 --> 00:15:16.615 align:middle line:84%
the name of the doctors
escapes me,

00:15:16.615 --> 00:15:19.452 align:middle line:84%
the famous Russian doctor
who's brought the notion

00:15:19.452 --> 00:15:21.954 align:middle line:84%
of water birth to the
rest of the western world.

00:15:21.954 --> 00:15:23.756 align:middle line:84%
She was his protege
and she explained

00:15:23.756 --> 00:15:27.526 align:middle line:84%
to me what the birth process
was like in Soviet Russia

00:15:27.526 --> 00:15:32.298 align:middle line:84%
which explained a lot of
things which was you go

00:15:32.298 --> 00:15:36.535 align:middle line:84%
into the center, you are
alone in the labor process.

00:15:36.535 --> 00:15:38.771 align:middle line:84%
There are other factors
before this that set you off,

00:15:38.771 --> 00:15:40.573 align:middle line:84%
but you are alone in
the labor process.

00:15:40.573 --> 00:15:43.909 align:middle line:84%
When the baby is finally
birth, the baby is taken away

00:15:43.909 --> 00:15:46.012 align:middle line:90%
for five days right immediately.

00:15:46.012 --> 00:15:48.581 align:middle line:84%
There's no bonding to
happen with the mother

00:15:48.581 --> 00:15:50.916 align:middle line:84%
which is excruciatingly
painful for her

00:15:50.916 --> 00:15:52.184 align:middle line:84%
with the nursing
and all of that.

00:15:52.184 --> 00:15:55.287 align:middle line:84%
But also the baby is
put on sugar water

00:15:55.287 --> 00:16:02.728 align:middle line:84%
and there is a complete lack of
bonding that would happen there.

00:16:02.728 --> 00:16:05.131 align:middle line:84%
And you start looking
at some of this larger--

00:16:05.131 --> 00:16:08.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean you call them
conspiracies, agendas,

00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:12.171 align:middle line:84%
whatever you want, this media
affects that keep people

00:16:12.171 --> 00:16:16.142 align:middle line:84%
in this isolated separateness
from one another competing

00:16:16.142 --> 00:16:17.643 align:middle line:90%
when that's against nature--

00:16:17.643 --> 00:16:19.011 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Right.

00:16:19.011 --> 00:16:20.513 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- with one another,
and you have to look at that

00:16:20.513 --> 00:16:22.214 align:middle line:90%
and say, "Hmm, it's all around.

00:16:22.214 --> 00:16:23.449 align:middle line:90%
It feels ground."

00:16:23.449 --> 00:16:27.219 align:middle line:84%
All the indications are
there to compete, separate,

00:16:27.219 --> 00:16:29.021 align:middle line:90%
become better than, isolated,

00:16:29.021 --> 00:16:31.891 align:middle line:84%
I can do it on my
own, wrong messaging.

00:16:31.891 --> 00:16:33.225 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: Well I think
it's more than wrong.

00:16:33.225 --> 00:16:35.828 align:middle line:84%
I think it's barbaric
and pathological.

00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:36.962 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: I agree.

00:16:36.962 --> 00:16:38.931 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: And it goes
against their instincts

00:16:38.931 --> 00:16:44.336 align:middle line:84%
at which were born, which is
to coalesce and come together.

00:16:44.336 --> 00:16:46.105 align:middle line:90%
We have to get beyond this.

00:16:46.105 --> 00:16:50.009 align:middle line:84%
Because this emphasis
on isolation

00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:53.145 align:middle line:84%
and disconnectedness I think
it's found this epidemic

00:16:53.145 --> 00:16:57.450 align:middle line:84%
of selfishness and greed which
at this point is no exaggeration

00:16:57.450 --> 00:17:01.420 align:middle line:84%
to say threatens their planet
and unless we can bond in a way

00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:04.457 align:middle line:84%
that helps us connect
with all cinch of life,

00:17:04.457 --> 00:17:05.725 align:middle line:84%
I don't think we
are going to be able

00:17:05.725 --> 00:17:08.060 align:middle line:84%
to meet the challenges
we face environmentally

00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:11.497 align:middle line:84%
and in many other ways and
there's search for ways

00:17:11.497 --> 00:17:13.666 align:middle line:90%
to survive as a species.

00:17:13.666 --> 00:17:15.668 align:middle line:84%
I don't think this
one as an bonded

00:17:15.668 --> 00:17:20.372 align:middle line:84%
and stuff is just a
matter for philosophy.

00:17:20.372 --> 00:17:23.875 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is not something
to be contemplated at leisure.

00:17:23.875 --> 00:17:26.077 align:middle line:90%
I think is an urgent situation.

00:17:26.077 --> 00:17:29.582 align:middle line:84%
I think their future depends
on whether we get it or not

00:17:29.582 --> 00:17:32.685 align:middle line:84%
about our connectedness, not
with just each other human

00:17:32.685 --> 00:17:35.321 align:middle line:84%
to human but with all the
rest of cinch in life.

00:17:35.321 --> 00:17:37.189 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Let's
talk about that,

00:17:37.189 --> 00:17:39.925 align:middle line:84%
the global coherence initiative,
Howard Martin's work.

00:17:39.925 --> 00:17:42.695 align:middle line:84%
There-- it's putting these
sensors around the planet

00:17:42.695 --> 00:17:46.932 align:middle line:84%
and these sensors are showing
the responds of the earth

00:17:46.932 --> 00:17:49.969 align:middle line:84%
to group thought
feeling and meditation.

00:17:49.969 --> 00:17:54.507 align:middle line:84%
We-- our emotional
body is intertwined

00:17:54.507 --> 00:17:56.909 align:middle line:84%
with the earth's
own emotional body.

00:17:56.909 --> 00:17:59.245 align:middle line:84%
And I know for some people
that's hard to imagine,

00:17:59.245 --> 00:18:03.516 align:middle line:84%
but this is as ancient being
that we lived with and on,

00:18:03.516 --> 00:18:06.552 align:middle line:84%
and we are-- is our
host let's say.

00:18:06.552 --> 00:18:07.753 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Well,

00:18:07.753 --> 00:18:09.855 align:middle line:84%
it's appropriate they were
filming this for Gaiam

00:18:09.855 --> 00:18:12.191 align:middle line:84%
because if there's
a television network

00:18:12.191 --> 00:18:16.529 align:middle line:84%
that has ever honored connected
and unity it is this one.

00:18:16.529 --> 00:18:18.164 align:middle line:90%
And so it's totally appropriate

00:18:18.164 --> 00:18:19.565 align:middle line:84%
that we're talking
about this here.

00:18:19.565 --> 00:18:22.134 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Yes, it's
absolutely is and it is,

00:18:22.134 --> 00:18:24.637 align:middle line:84%
it's being scientifically
proven if we put

00:18:24.637 --> 00:18:27.640 align:middle line:84%
out a particular thought process
that is of a negative nature,

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:30.309 align:middle line:84%
it is going to create
a stress within--

00:18:30.309 --> 00:18:32.578 align:middle line:84%
whatever the lay lines
are, the energetics

00:18:32.578 --> 00:18:34.914 align:middle line:84%
of that particular region
of the world, right?

00:18:34.914 --> 00:18:35.548 align:middle line:90%
>> Dossey: Right.

00:18:35.548 --> 00:18:36.949 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: I mean.

00:18:36.949 --> 00:18:38.617 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: Talk about something
called the global consciousness

00:18:38.617 --> 00:18:42.388 align:middle line:84%
project in the book which once
again has the sensor distributed

00:18:42.388 --> 00:18:43.989 align:middle line:90%
all over the planet.

00:18:43.989 --> 00:18:46.725 align:middle line:84%
And when an event
happens that have

00:18:46.725 --> 00:18:52.031 align:middle line:84%
to captures universal awareness
such as the World Cup and soccer

00:18:52.031 --> 00:18:57.970 align:middle line:84%
or Princess Diana's death,
the sensors begin to show

00:18:57.970 --> 00:19:01.340 align:middle line:84%
that the things become
more coherent

00:19:01.340 --> 00:19:03.776 align:middle line:84%
when they are producing
supposedly random

00:19:03.776 --> 00:19:05.377 align:middle line:84%
and equal numbers
of ones and zeros.

00:19:05.377 --> 00:19:09.982 align:middle line:84%
They begin to become
focused so do this electric--

00:19:09.982 --> 00:19:12.751 align:middle line:84%
electronic devices
in the same way

00:19:12.751 --> 00:19:14.853 align:middle line:84%
that people's minds
are being focused

00:19:14.853 --> 00:19:17.656 align:middle line:84%
on this particular event
whatever it might be.

00:19:17.656 --> 00:19:21.560 align:middle line:84%
This is a profound example of
this process of entanglement

00:19:21.560 --> 00:19:23.629 align:middle line:84%
that we were talking
about a moment ago.

00:19:23.629 --> 00:19:27.299 align:middle line:84%
And this is just crucial for
us to realize that when we talk

00:19:27.299 --> 00:19:28.500 align:middle line:90%
about our oneness and unity,

00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:32.137 align:middle line:84%
we're just not talking
woo-woo philosophy here.

00:19:32.137 --> 00:19:33.339 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: No.

00:19:33.339 --> 00:19:35.774 align:middle line:84%
>> Dossey: This has been
elevated now to the domain

00:19:35.774 --> 00:19:38.577 align:middle line:84%
of science and we have to
keep coming back to this

00:19:38.577 --> 00:19:40.145 align:middle line:84%
that we are making
this stuff up.

00:19:40.145 --> 00:19:43.082 align:middle line:84%
This is not poetic beautiful
metaphors when we talk

00:19:43.082 --> 00:19:44.450 align:middle line:90%
about unity and oneness.

